        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 2:50AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 250 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Knoxville, or 8 miles southeast of Clarksville, moving east at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lutherville...                    Dublin...
Long Pool Campground...           Ludwig...
Piney Bay Recreation Area...      Pleasant Valley in Pope County...
Broomfield...                     Caglesville...
Oak Grove in Pope County...       Augsburg...
Dover...                          Lake Dardanelle...
Delaware...                       Knoxville...
Gum Log...                        Lamar...
Moreland...                       London...
New Blaine...                     Tokalon...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
